The paper deals with a string matching problem and proposes a new index construction method that is based on the run-length encoding of the input string. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the time complexity of the index construction and query algorithms, which indicates that it may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category. The paper also characterizes the index in terms of prefix normal forms, which suggests that it may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of run-length encoding and the analysis of the index size and query time may also make the paper relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
